  "body": "See #1630 for the details, but the bottom line is that the message\r\n\r\n```\r\n     Error: Transaction reverted: function selector was not recognized and there's no fallback nor receive function\r\n```\r\n\r\nis a bit misleading when there's no calldata. My first guess is that we should have two different messages: one for when there _is_ a selector (and ideally we should show it) and another for when there is not.",
